<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-01T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="864" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d864">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.116/6: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-01T17:00:00+01:00">March
                                        1, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 5:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>279. Department’s 135, February 27, 11 a.m. Lagarde<note n="46" xml:id="d864fn46">Antoine Lagarde, Deputy Director of the Office
                                    of Near East and African Affairs, French Ministry for Foreign
                                    Affairs.</note> has promised to look without delay into the
                                question of exemption from exchange and import restrictions of
                                American goods ordered before December 3. He freely admits the force
                                of the argument that the restrictions should not apply to goods on
                                order before the effective date of the Syrian control and has given
                                us to understand that he will do his utmost to obtain a satisfactory
                                decision.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>